# Authentication Build and Organization

## Session design
- Use JWT session cookies managed in `src/app/lib/session.ts`.
- Cookie must be `httpOnly`, `secure`, `sameSite=lax`, and path-rooted.
- Session payload must include `userId`, role, role-specific id, and expiration metadata.

## Auth action boundaries
- Keep login/signup/logout and identity reads in user-centric server actions.
- Validate form payloads with Zod before DB access.
- Never expose password hashes or sensitive auth internals to client components.

## Access checks
- Verify session before protected data reads/writes.
- Enforce role checks in actions, not only in UI.
- Return typed errors or action state payloads that components can render safely.

## Routing behavior
- Public entry points (landing/login/signup) must redirect authenticated users away from auth screens.
- Protected pages must fail closed when session verification fails.
